Local SELinux policy module directory
=====================================

This directory is the staging area for locally-written SELinux policy modules.

Locally-installed modules have priority 400 by default.

 To see modules & their priorities:

  # semodule -lfull | grep '^400\s'

Modules can be installed for the fist time, or replaced with a newer version,
with the same command:

  # semodule -i mymodule.cil

To remove a module:

  # semodule -r mymodule
